Object oreinted programming is based on the concept of object which are instance of classes

oop allows as to structure our codes in a way that model real world entities using data(attributes) and behaviour(methods)

##why we used 
for modularity
for reusability
it well organized
it allows us to represent real world entites more natually 
##four pilliars of oop##
Encapsulation
inheritance
polermorphism
abstraction

##classes
classes are the blueprint or template for creating objects.it defined the properties or attributes and behaviours(methods) that the objects will have
object is an instances of a class , u can create multiple object of a class